    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This function provides a way to customize the built-in fade effect that Quartz performs when displays are reconfigured. The default time settings for this fade effect are 0.3 seconds to fade out, and 0.5 seconds to fade back in. The default fade color is French Blue for a normal desktop, and black for a captured display."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Before using this function, you need to call "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/1455235-cgbegindisplayconfiguration"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to acquire the display configuration token for the desired display. No fade reservation is needed—when you call "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/1454488-cgcompletedisplayconfiguration"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", Quartz reserves the fade hardware (assuming it is available) and performs the fade."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Calling this function modifies the fade behavior for a single display configuration and has no permanent effect."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
